'''Duskwood''' was a type of [[Wood/Legends|wood]].<ref name="Outbound">[[Outbound Flight (novel)|''Outbound Flight'']]</ref> In [[27 BBY/Legends|27 BBY]],<ref name="Date">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of [[Outbound Flight (novel)|''Outbound Flight'']] to [[27 BBY/Legends|27 BBY]].</ref> the [[Panky's]] [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]] on<ref name="Outbound" /> the [[Inner Rim/Legends|Inner Rim]]<ref name="EAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}} &mdash; Based on corresponding data for [[Barlok system/Legends|Barlok system]]</ref> [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Barlok/Legends|Barlok]] had a genuine duskwood bartop, a fact that was noticed by the visiting [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]].<ref name="Outbound" />

==Behind the scenes==
Duskwood appeared in [[Timothy Zahn]]'s [[2006]] novel [[Outbound Flight (novel)|''Outbound Flight'']].<ref name="Outbound" />

